A Twitter user, Oge Kings, has shared a letter listing the items expected from him for the burial of his landlord. Kings shared the letter on Twitter in response to a viral letter purportedly written by the Oluwo of Iwo, Oba Abdulrosheed Akanbi, asking the Osun State Government for money for his wedding to a Kano princess.   Block illicit financial flows to reduce debt accumulation,…     Police arrest couple with severed breasts, hands, other…     FG reiterates commitment to completion of road projects    He shared the letter addressed to him with the caption: “You never see anything sef. My landlord just died and his son wrote a list of items that I will give to him as his tenant for his burial rites.” Part of the items he’s expected to provide include a live goat, N100,000, malt drinks and alcoholic drinks, among others. SPONSORED